    <section>
        <h2>The negatives:</h2>
        <p><strong>Rates of production:</strong> with the increase in technology and the creation of
            more
            sophisticated machinery/tools, we can easily mass produce most needed products
            with far more efficiency than before and far faster as well. Though it does serve as an
            answer to the
            constant
            increase of demand to satisfy Human needs,
            this can cause a quicker depletion of natural and limited resources, if we are the overexert
            the
            collection/gathering of primary materials they will eventually become scarce or vanish.</p>
        <br />
        <p><strong>Waste:</strong> As we are mass producing more, so are we creating more waste either
            from
            leftovers of some primary material that just doesnt serve to be used in the creation of a
            certain
            product
            or via the very own process of the desired products creation resulting into unneeded waste
            (some of
            which
            can
            be toxic) that cannot be of any use.</p>
        <p>With the increase in waste and the lack of proper developed ways to dispose of it, this can
            result in
            a
            plethora of problems such as illegal dumpings or overcostly methods of disposal due to lack
            of
            proper developed ways to take care of such.(this topic was talked before in the pillars of
            sustainability,
            one
            must have eyes for the future to achieve a greener economy).</p>
        <br />
        <p><strong>Polution:</strong> This one is pretty self explanatory, with technological
            advancements and
            production of more/other types of machinery it will all result in a lot more pollution
            which,
            affect global warming which can furter result in disruptive changes towards the environment
            resulting
            it a
            completely chaotic and non-sustainable ecosystem which we are also a part of.</p>
