        <h2>The positives:</h2>
        <div>
            <p><strong>Renewable energy:</strong> Of course not all technology is bad for the
                environment nor the
                sustainability of our planet and society, there are multiple ways of harnessing energy
                for means of
                production,
                and even though right now the most efficient one might be the burning of fossil
                fuels(efficient as
                in if
                your main goal is just obtaining energy), that does not mean that in the future this
                won't change.
            </p>
            <p>It will change, sustainability is about meeting the needs of the present without
                compromising the
                future
                ones and this never was a sustainable method.</p>
            <p>But there are other ways of obtaining energy without the need of limited resources, we
                can opt for
                renewable
                ones instead such has such has sunlight, wind, waves, tides and even geothermal heat.
            </p>
            <p>Modern environmental technology has enabled us to capture this naturally occurring energy
                and
                convert it
                into electricity through devices such as solar panels, wind and water turbines, etc.</p>
            <p>With these never ending resources, and the correct advancement in technology, it is
                possible to
                achive a
                sustainable mean that will fill our needs and not injure the ones who come after.</p>
